n*Gooseworx\n*Thomas Ryan\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 1\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = Vivienne Medrano\n| news_editor              = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = Vivienne Medrano\n| camera                   = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime                  = 30 minutes\n| company                  = SpindleHorse Toons\n| channel                  = \n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = [[YouTube]]\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|10|28}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = ''Helluva Boss''\n| website                  = https://www.hazbinhotel.com/\n| website_title            = Official Website \n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''Hazbin Hotel''''' is an American [[Adult animation|adult animated]] [[musical film|musical]] [[black comedy]] [[web series]] created, directed, written and produced by Vivienne \"Vivziepop\" Medrano.<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /><ref name=\"Belatina\"/> The official [[Television pilot|pilot]] was released on [[YouTube]] on October 28, 2019.<ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /> On November 6, 2019, Medrano stated on [[Patreon]] that there was no stated release date for a second episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patreon.com/posts/wowza-we-did-it-31353812|title=WOWZA!! WE DID IT!! (UPDATE)|last=Medrano|first=Vivienne|date=November 6, 2019|website=Patreon|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref>\n\nThe series' protagonist, Charlie, is the princess of [[Hell]] with the goal of rehabilitating [[sin]]ners in the titular 'Hazbin Hotel,' as a peaceful alternative of reducing the population other than [[genocide]].<ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" />\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows the misadventures of Charlie (Jill Harris), the princess of Hell and heir to the throne as she sets about fulfilling her dream of opening up a hotel called the \"Happy Hotel\" which aims to rehabilitate [[sin]]ners. Due to overpopulation, the citizens go through an annual \"cleanse\", arranged by angels. Her main goal is hoping that her clients will be \"checking out\u201c peacefully into Heaven. With the help of her devoted manager and girlfriend Vaggie (Monica Franco) and their first patron, [[pornographic film actor]] Angel Dust (Michael Kovach), she's determined to make her dream become a reality. But when her proposal on live television goes sour, her plan attracts the attention of the powerful \"radio demon entity\" Alastor (Edward Bosco) who, despite finding her belief in redemption laughable, wants to help Charlie run the hotel for his own amusement.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lillie |first1=David |title=Hazbin Hotel\u2019s Upcoming Premiere & The Crowdfunding Frontier |url=https://bleedingfool.com/movies-tv-film/hazbin-hotels-upcoming-premiere-the-crowdfunding-frontier/ |website=Bleeding Fool |accessdate=29 October 2019 |date=25 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Peters |first1=Danielle |title=\"Animation is Magic\": SVA Alumnus VivziePop on Perseverance, Inspiration and 'Hazbin Hotel' |url=http://www.sva.edu/features/animation-is-magic-sva-alumnus-vivziepop-on-perseverance-inspiration-and-hazbin-hotel |website=SVA NYC |publisher=School of Visual Arts |accessdate=29 October 2019 |date=15 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/features/news-bytes-sarah-duck-quacks-back-in-us-check-in-to-hazbin-hotel-tellys-get-immersive-more/ | title=News Bytes: \u2018Sarah & Duck\u2019 Quacks Back in US, Check in to \u2018Hazbin Hotel,\u2019 Tellys Get Immersive & More | author=Milligan, Mercedes | website=Animation Magazine | date=30 October 2019 | accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\nThis is a pro-mo for the channel \u201cEmKay\u201d go watch him please\n\n==Characters==\n===Main characters===\n*'''{{vanchor|Charlotte \"Charlie\" Magne}}'''<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\">{{cite tweet |user= HazbinHotel | number= 992872171272732672 | date= 5 May 2018 | accessdate=7 February 2020 | title= We want to help everyone get to know our cast! So today we are sharing some official info!no}}</ref> (voiced by Jill Harris; singing voice by Elsie Lovelock) is one of the main protagonists and founder of Hazbin Hotel (originally named Happy Hotel). She is the daughter of [[Satan|Lucifer]] and [[Lilith]], and is one of the few demons born in Hell. Upset by the yearly cleanse in which a number of demons are destroyed by the Exterminators, she and her girlfriend<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"Belatina\"/> Vaggie seek to open a hotel that allows for the rehabilitation of sinners with the hope that they can receive forgiveness and enter heaven. Her bold plans are often laughed at by most of the demons in hell. She is shown to be very naive and optimistic but cares deeply for her people. She has a love for [[musical theatre]], preferring expressing herself in singing and dance, and has had an ex-boyfriend in the past.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n*'''{{vanchor|Vagatha \"Vaggie\"}}''' (voiced by Monica Franco) is Charlie's girlfriend<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"Belatina\">{{Cite web|url=https://belatina.com/hazbin-hotel-pilot-review/|title=A Salvadoran-American Artist\u2019s Conception of Hell|last=Liberman|first=Dr Esther|date=2019-12-09|website=BeLatina|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> and the Manager<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> of the Hazbin Hotel. She is highly supportive of Charlie and has a quick temper. Often acting as the more level-headed and rational one, she struggles to keep the hotel's image up. She is quite annoyed by Angel Dust's trouble-making and doesn't trust Alastor at all due to his notorious reputation. She is often shown defending Charlie with a large spear similar to that of the Exterminators. She can also summon various knives and daggers at will. There is little information about her past life, but it is known that she entered Hell in 2014.<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/>\n*'''{{vanchor|Anthony \"Angel Dust\"}}''' (voiced by Michael Kovach) is a four-armed [[Androgyny|androgynous]] [[Pornographic film actor|adult-film star]], and the first volunteer for Charlie's rehabilitation program. He doesn't seem to take Charlie's cause seriously, stating to only be interested in the [[renting|rent]]-free accommodation, much to Vaggie's anger, and tends to get into mischief behind their backs. In his mortal life, Angel was born to a [[Organized crime|crime family]],<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> most of which reside in hell with him.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Angel struggled with drug addiction{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} which ultimately led to his death in 1947.<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> His stage name is based on the street name for the drug [[Phencyclidine]], which he still regularly uses in Hell.\n*'''{{vanchor|Alastor}}''', also known as the \"'''Radio Demon'''\" (voiced by Edward Bosco; singing voice by Gabriel C. Brown), is an eccentric demon Overlord. Known to be extremely powerful and is capable of rivaling some of Hell's most ancient demons, despite having been a [[wiktionary:mortal|mortal]] [[human]] in life. Upon his arrival in hell he built up a terrifying reputation seemingly overnight. Often keeping to a calm and gentlemanly demeanor, he prefers to always keep a smile on his face and shares Charlie's love of music and dance. His voice sounds like a vintage 1920s radio complete with static, sound effects including a [[laugh track]], and theme music. He offers his services to Charlie in order to help her maintain her goal of running the hotel, but only for the amusement of watching other demons fail in the process. Charlie reluctantly allows his services as long as he doesn't do anything to jeopardize the hotel, and for as long as he chooses without making one of his [[Deal with the Devil|infamous pacts]], and by also invoking her status as the heir to the throne. He nevertheless, provides a staff, and protects Charlie's business from outside threats. It's stated that in his past life, Alastor was an actual [[Radio broadcasting|radio announcer]] who lived a double life as a [[serial killer]] in the [[Deep South]].<ref name=\"Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\"/> Having lived to see the [[Great Depression|Stock market crash]], he died in 1933.<ref name=\"Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\">{{cite tweet |user= HazbinHotel | number= 992879031182704640 | date= 6 May 2018 | accessdate=13 February 2020 | title= Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\ud83d\ude08}}</ref>\n* '''Niffty''' (voiced by Michelle Marie) is a small, fast demonic [[cyclops]] from the 1950s.{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} who's obsessed with cleanliness. She is summoned by Alastor to serve as the hotel housekeeper. She has bubbly and friendly demeanor and is very helpful.\n* '''Husk \"Husker\"''' (voiced by Mick Lauer), an ill-tempered and alcoholic 70s-era,{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} cat demon. He is summoned by Alastor to serve as the receptionist and bartender at the hotel. He seems to have a long history with Alastor, and is often displeased with being dragged into another one of his schemes.\n\n===Guest characters===\n* '''[[Lucifer]]''' and '''[[Lilith]]''' '''Magne''': Charlie's parents are only mentioned and displayed in a family portrait. Like Charlie, their appearance isn't fearsome and could almost pass as \"human\". Visual nods to their character designs are present; such as Lucifer's staff being a clear reference to [[Adam and Eve#The Fall|his tempting of Eve]]. Vivienne has described Lucifer as a [[Willy Wonka|Willy Wonka-like]] character,{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} and if he and Alastor met, they would be good friends due to their matching personalities.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Lilith is shown in portraits and posters to be a famous [[Theatre|stage performer]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} explaining Charlie's love of music and dance. She also appears to be the more understanding of Charlie's goals{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} while Lucifer doesn't believe Charlie's plan would work.\n\n==Episodes==\n===Pilot (2019)===\n{{Episode table\n| total_width = \n| background = #3CB371\n| overall = \n| title = \n| director = \n| writer = \n| airdate = \n| aux2=\n| aux2T=Storyboarded by\n| prodcode = \n| prodcodeR = \n| country = U.S.\n| episodes =\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = That's Entertainment\n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = Vivienne Medrano\n| WrittenBy       = Vivienne Medrano, Dave Capdevielle & Raymond Hernandez\n| Aux2            = Vivienne Medrano\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|28}}\n| ProdCode        = \n| ShortSummary    = Charlie, the princess of Hell, and her girlfriend Vaggie, open a hotel in an effort to \"rehabilitate\" demons. Her plans to promote the Happy Hotel on the news backfires after Angel Dust, the hotel's only patron, gets into a fight with Sir Pentious on live television. After a brief argument on their way to the hotel, they're visited by Alastor, a notorious demon overlord who seeks to help Charlie with the hotel. Despite his shady claims that he only wishes to provide this \"charity\" for his own entertainment, Charlie allows his help for as long as he wishes, and to not do anything that would ruin her goals. Alastor accepts and provides her with a staff to help run the hotel, he defeats Sir Pentious when he attacks the hotel seeking revenge, and changes the name from Happy to Hazbin Hotel after inviting everyone back inside to have [[jambalaya]].<hr>Songs: \"I'm Always Chasing Rainbows\" ''(Charlie)'', \"Inside of Every Demon Is a Rainbow\" ''(Charlie)'', \"Alastor's Reprise\" ''(Alastor)''\n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n<!---\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       =\n| Aux2            =\n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   =\n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| Aux2            = \n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n===Season 2===--->\n}}\n\n==Other media==\n===Comic===\nVivziepop announced a prequel comic focusing on the characters prior to the events of the series.<ref name=\"7 MILLION? WHATS NEXT?\">{{cite web | url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=s4RKc83V19E | title=7 MILLION? WHATS NEXT? BIG OL UPDATE VIDYO!! | date=11 November 2019 | author=Vivziepop | website=YouTube | accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref> As of October 2019, there are seven pages hosted on the official website.<ref name=\"7 MILLION? WHATS NEXT?\"/>\n\n===''Helluva Boss''===\n''Helluva Boss'' is a standalone animated web series set in the same universe as ''Hazbin Hotel'' but with a different voice cast and story, co-written and starring YouTuber Brandon Rogers. It focuses around the enthusiastic imp Blitzo (voiced by Rogers) and his subordinate employees\u2014Moxxie, Millie (Moxxie's wife), and Loona (Blitzo's adopted daughter and receptionist)\u2014running an assassination agency called the Immediate Murder Professionals (IMP).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OlahNrlcgS4|title=HELLUVA BOSS (PILOT)|author=Vivziepop|date=25 November 2019|via=YouTube|accessdate=26 December 2019}}</ref> Moxxie is voiced by [[Richard Steven Horvitz]], while both Millie and Loona are voiced by [[Erica Lindbeck]].<ref>{{Citation|title=HELLUVA BOSS (PILOT)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OlahNrlcgS4|language=en|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> Blitzo stole the book to make a portal to the living world from [[List of demons in the Ars Goetia#Stolas|Stolas]] (voiced by Brock Baker), one of the Overlords of Hell, and the group later kills Eddie (voiced by Horvitz), a male child. Writing production for more episodes began in December 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet |user= VivziePop | number= 1211424101010534401 | date= 29 December 2019 | accessdate=7 February 2020 | title= I'm thrilled to say me and @BrandonLOVESYOU are getting started on writing more #HelluvaBoss!!!}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Hazbin Hotel'' has been generally well received by critics for its animation quality, music and characters.<ref name=\":0\" /> [[WhatCulture.com]] praised the animation quality in ''Hazbin Hotel'', noting that it \"doesn't just mark the debut of a fun, funny, stylish new (and mature) animated feature \u2014 it also shows the high-quality work even a small team of animators can create without need for the executive interference of a bigger company getting in the way of independent creative freedom.\u201d<ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\">{{Cite web|url=http://whatculture.com/tv/hazbin-hotel-review-the-surprise-indie-animated-hit-of-2019|title=Hazbin Hotel Review: The Surprise Indie Animated Hit Of 2019|first=Motzie|last=Dapul|date=October 31, 2019|website=WhatCulture.com}}</ref> Stephen Novak from [[The Oswegonian]] student newspaper praised the animation, writing, and characters in ''Hazbin Hotel'', but criticized the songs, saying \"While \"''Hazbin Hotel''\" will certainly not appeal to everyone, those who can appreciate good animation and fun characters will certainly find themselves tortured by what is likely to be a long wait until the next episode.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web | url=https://www.oswegonian.com/2019/11/07/hazbin-hotel-debuts-with-masterful-animation-strong-writing/ | title=\u2018Hazbin Hotel\u2019 Debuts With Masterful Animation, Strong Writing | author=Novak, Stephen | date=7 November 2019 | website=The Oswegonian | accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|url=https://www.hazbinhotel.com/}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zlmswo0S0e0 Official Hazbin Hotel Pilot] on YouTube\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CeOWxqYp80A Official Hazbin Hotel Trailer] on YouTube\n*{{IMDb title|7216636}}\n*[https://m.imdb.com/title/tt10691770/ ''Helluva Boss''] on IMDb\n*[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=OlahNrlcgS4 Helluva Boss Official Pilot] on YouTube\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2rzBpIU-L78 Official \"Helluva Boss\" Trailer] on YouTube\n{{Portal bar|Animation|Cartoon|United States|Comedy|Music|Horror fiction}}\n\n[[Category:American adult animated web series]]\n[[Category:2010s black comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American horror comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American surreal comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American musical comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2019 web series debuts]]\n[[Category:American adult animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American adult animated drama television series]]\n[[Category:American adult animated horror television series]]\n[[Category:American adult animated musical television series]]\n[[Category:American television pilots]]\n[[Category:Fiction about the afterlife]]\n[[Category:Drama web series]]\n[[Category:Drama webtoons]]\n[[Category:Hell in popular culture]]\n[[Category:Demons in television]]\n[[Category:Independent animation]]\n[[Category:Surreal comedy]]\n[[Category:Sitcom web series]]\n[[Category:Comedy horror web series]]\n[[Category:Drama webcomics]]\n[[Category:American comedy webcomics]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related animated web series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series set in hotels]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Television programs adapted into comics]]\n[[Category:Television series about demons]]\n[[Category:Horror fiction web series]]\n[[Category:Comedy-drama web series]]\n[[Category:Genocide in fiction]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American adult animated musical sitcom}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Third-party|date=November 2019}}\n{{More citations needed|date=February 2020}}\n}}{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Hazbin Hotel\n| image                    = Hazbin Hotel opening credits.jpeg\n| alt                      = Title card\n| caption                  = \n| | genre                  = [[Adult animation]]<ref name=\"geekiary\">{{cite web | url=https://thegeekiary.com/hazbin-hotel-review/73056 | title=Hazbin Hotel: The Queer Demon Princess Revue\u2026 Review | author=Bekah | date=9 November 2019 | website=The Geekiary | accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /><br>\n[[Musical fiction|Musical]]<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\">{{cite web | url=https://www.goexpress.co.za/2019/12/05/hazbin-Hotel-marks-a-turning-point-for-indie-animation/ | title=\u2018Hazbin Hotel\u2019 a bold step in indie animation | author=Matthew Field | date=5 December 2019 | website=Go! & Express | accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /><br>\n[[Black comedy]]<ref name=\"Belatina\"/>\n| creator                  = Vivienne Medrano\n| writer                   = Vivienne Medrano<br />Dave Capdevielle<br />Raymond Hernandez<br />Daniel Macdonald<br />Kendraw Cook\n| screenplay               = Vivienne Medrano\n| story                    = Vivienne Medrano\n| director                 = Vivienne Medrano\n| creative_director        = Vivienne Medrano\n| voices                   = {{plainlist|\n*Jill Harris\n*Monica Franco\n*Michael Kovach\n*Edward Bosco\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = {{plainlist|\n*[[Harry Carroll]]\n*[[Joseph McCarthy (lyricist)|Joseph McCarthy]]\n}}\n| opentheme                = [[I'm Always Chasing Rainbows]] (pilot)\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = {{plainlist|\n*Vivienne Medrano\n*Evan Alderete\n*Gooseworx\n*Thomas Ryan\n}}\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 1\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = Vivienne Medrano\n| news_editor              = \n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = Vivienne Medrano\n| camera                   = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime                  = 30 minutes\n| company                  = SpindleHorse Toons\n| channel                  = \n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = [[YouTube]]\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|10|28}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = ''Helluva Boss''\n| website                  = https://www.hazbinhotel.com/\n| website_title            = Official Website \n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''Hazbin Hotel''''' is an American [[Adult animation|adult animated]] [[musical film|musical]] [[black comedy]] [[web series]] created, directed, written and produced by Vivienne \"Vivziepop\" Medrano.<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /><ref name=\"Belatina\"/> The official [[Television pilot|pilot]] was released on [[YouTube]] on October 28, 2019.<ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" /> On November 6, 2019, Medrano stated on [[Patreon]] that there was no stated release date for a second episode.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patreon.com/posts/wowza-we-did-it-31353812|title=WOWZA!! WE DID IT!! (UPDATE)|last=Medrano|first=Vivienne|date=November 6, 2019|website=Patreon|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref>\n\nThe series' protagonist, Charlie, is the princess of [[Hell]] with the goal of rehabilitating [[sin]]ners in the titular 'Hazbin Hotel,' as a peaceful alternative of reducing the population other than [[genocide]].<ref name=\"The Surprise Indie Hit Of 2019\" />\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows the misadventures of Charlie (Jill Harris), the princess of Hell and heir to the throne as she sets about fulfilling her dream of opening up a hotel called the \"Happy Hotel\" which aims to rehabilitate [[sin]]ners. Due to overpopulation, the citizens go through an annual \"cleanse\", arranged by angels. Her main goal is hoping that her clients will be \"checking out\u201c peacefully into Heaven. With the help of her devoted manager and girlfriend Vaggie (Monica Franco) and their first patron, [[pornographic film actor]] Angel Dust (Michael Kovach), she's determined to make her dream become a reality. But when her proposal on live television goes sour, her plan attracts the attention of the powerful \"radio demon entity\" Alastor (Edward Bosco) who, despite finding her belief in redemption laughable, wants to help Charlie run the hotel for his own amusement.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lillie |first1=David |title=Hazbin Hotel\u2019s Upcoming Premiere & The Crowdfunding Frontier |url=https://bleedingfool.com/movies-tv-film/hazbin-hotels-upcoming-premiere-the-crowdfunding-frontier/ |website=Bleeding Fool |accessdate=29 October 2019 |date=25 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Peters |first1=Danielle |title=\"Animation is Magic\": SVA Alumnus VivziePop on Perseverance, Inspiration and 'Hazbin Hotel' |url=http://www.sva.edu/features/animation-is-magic-sva-alumnus-vivziepop-on-perseverance-inspiration-and-hazbin-hotel |website=SVA NYC |publisher=School of Visual Arts |accessdate=29 October 2019 |date=15 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/features/news-bytes-sarah-duck-quacks-back-in-us-check-in-to-hazbin-hotel-tellys-get-immersive-more/ | title=News Bytes: \u2018Sarah & Duck\u2019 Quacks Back in US, Check in to \u2018Hazbin Hotel,\u2019 Tellys Get Immersive & More | author=Milligan, Mercedes | website=Animation Magazine | date=30 October 2019 | accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Characters==\n===Main characters===\n*'''{{vanchor|Charlotte \"Charlie\" Magne}}'''<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\">{{cite tweet |user= HazbinHotel | number= 992872171272732672 | date= 5 May 2018 | accessdate=7 February 2020 | title= We want to help everyone get to know our cast! So today we are sharing some official info!no}}</ref> (voiced by Jill Harris; singing voice by Elsie Lovelock) is one of the main protagonists and founder of Hazbin Hotel (originally named Happy Hotel). She is the daughter of [[Satan|Lucifer]] and [[Lilith]], and is one of the few demons born in Hell. Upset by the yearly cleanse in which a number of demons are destroyed by the Exterminators, she and her girlfriend<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"Belatina\"/> Vaggie seek to open a hotel that allows for the rehabilitation of sinners with the hope that they can receive forgiveness and enter heaven. Her bold plans are often laughed at by most of the demons in hell. She is shown to be very naive and optimistic but cares deeply for her people. She has a love for [[musical theatre]], preferring expressing herself in singing and dance, and has had an ex-boyfriend in the past.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n*'''{{vanchor|Vagatha \"Vaggie\"}}''' (voiced by Monica Franco) is Charlie's girlfriend<ref name=\"geekiary\"/><ref name=\"go\"/><ref name=\"Belatina\">{{Cite web|url=https://belatina.com/hazbin-hotel-pilot-review/|title=A Salvadoran-American Artist\u2019s Conception of Hell|last=Liberman|first=Dr Esther|date=2019-12-09|website=BeLatina|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> and the Manager<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> of the Hazbin Hotel. She is highly supportive of Charlie and has a quick temper. Often acting as the more level-headed and rational one, she struggles to keep the hotel's image up. She is quite annoyed by Angel Dust's trouble-making and doesn't trust Alastor at all due to his notorious reputation. She is often shown defending Charlie with a large spear similar to that of the Exterminators. She can also summon various knives and daggers at will. There is little information about her past life, but it is known that she entered Hell in 2014.<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/>\n*'''{{vanchor|Anthony \"Angel Dust\"}}''' (voiced by Michael Kovach) is a four-armed [[Androgyny|androgynous]] [[Pornographic film actor|adult-film star]], and the first volunteer for Charlie's rehabilitation program. He doesn't seem to take Charlie's cause seriously, stating to only be interested in the [[renting|rent]]-free accommodation, much to Vaggie's anger, and tends to get into mischief behind their backs. In his mortal life, Angel was born to a [[Organized crime|crime family]],<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> most of which reside in hell with him.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Angel struggled with drug addiction{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} which ultimately led to his death in 1947.<ref name=\"We want to help everyone get to know our cast!\"/> His stage name is based on the street name for the drug [[Phencyclidine]], which he still regularly uses in Hell.\n*'''{{vanchor|Alastor}}''', also known as the \"'''Radio Demon'''\" (voiced by Edward Bosco; singing voice by Gabriel C. Brown), is an eccentric demon Overlord. Known to be extremely powerful and is capable of rivaling some of Hell's most ancient demons, despite having been a [[wiktionary:mortal|mortal]] [[human]] in life. Upon his arrival in hell he built up a terrifying reputation seemingly overnight. Often keeping to a calm and gentlemanly demeanor, he prefers to always keep a smile on his face and shares Charlie's love of music and dance. His voice sounds like a vintage 1920s radio complete with static, sound effects including a [[laugh track]], and theme music. He offers his services to Charlie in order to help her maintain her goal of running the hotel, but only for the amusement of watching other demons fail in the process. Charlie reluctantly allows his services as long as he doesn't do anything to jeopardize the hotel, and for as long as he chooses without making one of his [[Deal with the Devil|infamous pacts]], and by also invoking her status as the heir to the throne. He nevertheless, provides a staff, and protects Charlie's business from outside threats. It's stated that in his past life, Alastor was an actual [[Radio broadcasting|radio announcer]] who lived a double life as a [[serial killer]] in the [[Deep South]].<ref name=\"Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\"/> Having lived to see the [[Great Depression|Stock market crash]], he died in 1933.<ref name=\"Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\">{{cite tweet |user= HazbinHotel | number= 992879031182704640 | date= 6 May 2018 | accessdate=13 February 2020 | title= Get to know some of the more devious of the cast!\ud83d\ude08}}</ref>\n* '''Niffty''' (voiced by Michelle Marie) is a small, fast demonic [[cyclops]] from the 1950s.{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} who's obsessed with cleanliness. She is summoned by Alastor to serve as the hotel housekeeper. She has bubbly and friendly demeanor and is very helpful.\n* '''Husk \"Husker\"''' (voiced by Mick Lauer), an ill-tempered and alcoholic 70s-era,{{Citation needed|date=February 2020}} cat demon. He is summoned by Alastor to serve as the receptionist and bartender at the hotel. He seems to have a long history with Alastor, and is often displeased with being dragged into another one of his schemes.\n\n===Guest characters===\n* '''[[Lucifer]]''' and '''[[Lilith]]''' '''Magne''': Charlie's parents are only mentioned and displayed in a family portrait. Like Charlie, their appearance isn't fearsome and could almost pass as \"human\". Visual nods to their character designs are present; such as Lucifer's staff being a clear reference to [[Adam and Eve#The Fall|his tempting of Eve]]. Vivienne has described Lucifer as a [[Willy Wonka|Willy Wonka-like]] character,{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} and if he and Alastor met, they would be good friends due to their matching personalities.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} Lilith is shown in portraits and posters to be a famous [[Theatre|stage performer]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} explaining Charlie's love of music and dance. She also appears to be the more understanding of Charlie's goals{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} while Lucifer doesn't believe Charlie's plan would work.\n\n==Episodes==\n===Pilot (2019)===\n{{Episode table\n| total_width = \n| background = #3CB371\n| overall = \n| title = \n| director = \n| writer = \n| airdate = \n| aux2=\n| aux2T=Storyboarded by\n| prodcode = \n| prodcodeR = \n| country = U.S.\n| episodes =\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = That's Entertainment\n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = Vivienne Medrano\n| WrittenBy       = Vivienne Medrano, Dave Capdevielle & Raymond Hernandez\n| Aux2            = Vivienne Medrano\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|28}}\n| ProdCode        = \n| ShortSummary    = Charlie, the princess of Hell, and her girlfriend Vaggie, open a hotel in an effort to \"rehabilitate\" demons. Her plans to promote the Happy Hotel on the news backfires after Angel Dust, the hotel's only patron, gets into a fight with Sir Pentious on live television. After a brief argument on their way to the hotel, they're visited by Alastor, a notorious demon overlord who seeks to help Charlie with the hotel. Despite his shady claims that he only wishes to provide this \"charity\" for his own entertainment, Charlie allows his help for as long as he wishes, and to not do anything that would ruin her goals. Alastor accepts and provides her with a staff to help run the hotel, he defeats Sir Pentious when he attacks the hotel seeking revenge, and changes the name from Happy to Hazbin Hotel after inviting everyone back inside to have [[jambalaya]].<hr>Songs: \"I'm Always Chasing Rainbows\" ''(Charlie)'', \"Inside of Every Demon Is a Rainbow\" ''(Charlie)'', \"Alastor's Reprise\" ''(Alastor)''\n| LineColor       = 3CB371\n}}\n<!---\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = \n| Title           = \n| RTitle          = \n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       =\n| Aux2            =\n| OriginalAirDate = \n| ProdCo